definitions.definition: One of the casks stowed in the wings of a vessel's hold, being smaller than such as are stowed more amidships .
examples: We hauled out a winger of grog.

definitions.definition: An offensive player who plays on either side of the center .
examples: The center passed to the left winger , who shot and scored.
